cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the energy efficiency of signal processing in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT), system and control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the distribution of signal processing operations and the development of decentralized and sustainable radio resource management techniques.
